The grinding wheels of  labor  fuel  the  economies and  markets  of  the world. Machines, factories and blue-collar workers line up in endless drudgery, churning  out the staples of everyday living. Control over Industry Influence sways the formation o f unions,  the movements of work projects,  locations for factories and the product of manufacturing concerns. Union workers, foremen, engineers, construction workers, manual laborers and all manner of blue-collar workers exist among these ranks.

