## Political

Garou don't do well in deals with bloodsucking leeches; they tend not to work with vampires, either. Altering party platforms, controlling local elections, changing appointed offices  and calling in  favors  all  falls  under the  purview o f  Political  Influence. Well-timed blackmail, bribery, spin doctoring or any sundry tricks are stock in trade on both sides of this fence. Some of the likely contacts and allies include pollsters, lobbyists, activists, party  members, spin doctors and politicians from rural  zoning committees to the mayors of major cities or Congressional representatives.

